This paper deals with the problem of learning vector-valued functions, which is a common task in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of local Rademacher complexity and unlabeled data is a novel approach to this problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions multi-label learning and multi-class classification, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of unlabeled data also suggests that the paper may be relevant to semi-supervised learning (cs.AI) and active learning (cs.SI).
